OL,4,CColin Pitchfork: MoJ sorry for sex
OL,5,Coffenders register error
OL,6, The Ministry of Justice has apologised
OL,7, for saying killer Colin Pitchfork would
OL,8, not have to sign the sex offenders
OL,9, register when released from prison.
OL,11,FA judge-led review backed up a Parole
OL,12,FBoard decision to allow the release of
OL,13,FPitchfork, who raped and strangled two
OL,14,Fteenagers in the 1980s.
OL,16,FOfficials had said the 61-year-old's
OL,17,Fcrimes predated the legislation.
OL,19,FThe department has now said this is not
OL,20,Fthe case and it "sincerely apologised"
OL,21,Ffor the error.
